The paper deals with the problem of breaking symmetries in decision problems, which is a common topic in computer science. The focus on generating sets and the use of lexicographical ordering constraints suggest a connection to discrete structures (cs.DS) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The mention of NP-hardness and the use of constraints also suggest connections to computational complexity (cs.CC) and constraint programming (cs.CG). Finally, the use of lexicographical ordering constraints suggests a connection to logic and verification (cs.LO).
